  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mrs. Sarah Blake Sturgis Shaw writes that her husband, Francis George Shaw, will no doubt contribute to the Liberty Bell. Mrs. Shaw explains that she has a strong distaste for lending her name &quot;to any advertisement for the public prints&quot; and therefore will not do so in connection with the fair.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The postscript on page three of this manuscript is signed by Francis George Shaw. He writes: &quot;Please hold me accountable for five Dollars which I will have much pleasure in handing to you before the fair.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
